{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:51:52.934Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Considering the Diagram**\n\nI'm quite pleased with the architecture diagram; it's visually appealing and truly engaging. I've shifted focus now to outlining the internal design for each page, starting with the **Agent Marketplace**, followed by **Runtime Governance**, and finally, the **Developer Platform**.\n\n\n**Defining Marketplace Details**\n\nI'm now diving into the precise components for the Agent Marketplace. I'm focusing on defining the required sections, layouts, metaphors, and interactions for this initial page. I want to ensure we're clear on how this page will be laid out, specifically the dynamic category selectors, the grid-based blueprints on the left, and the Inspector panel on the right.\n\n\n**Detailing Interaction Strategy**\n\nI'm now detailing the user interactions for the Agent Marketplace. Clicking a category filters agents in the Bento Grid. Selecting an agent populates the Inspector panel with details and a \"Deploy to Sandbox\" button. A loading state for this button transitions to \"Active in Sandbox.\" I'm also planning mobile responsiveness, ensuring the Inspector stacks appropriately. This will affect file changes to `app/platforms/agent-marketplace/page.tsx` and the aliasing of `app/platforms/marketplace/page.tsx`.\n\n\n**Outlining Governance Details**\n\nI'm now outlining the Runtime Governance details. I've defined the narrative around guardrails, emphasizing continuous observation and human oversight, which I'm calling a \"governance-first design\". I'm envisioning the \"Guardian Firewall\" as a visual metaphor and designing a layout with a hero section to showcase risk mitigation and an interactive \"Governance Shield\".\n\n\n**Defining Governance Mechanics**\n\nI'm now detailing the operational features for Runtime Governance. I'm focusing on \"Risk Firewalls,\" \"Human Oversight,\" and the \"Audit Ledger\" tabs within a tabbed component, each offering interactive visual blocks. I envision an interactive \"Governance Shield\" for clicking execution stages and toggling compliance policies. I'm also preparing mobile layouts with Tailwind's flex-col/grid and SVG scaling.\n\n\n**Defining Developer Platform**\n\nI'm now detailing the Developer Platform page. I've defined the narrative for senior engineers, emphasizing a robust command surface for multi-agent fabric design and simulation. The visual metaphor is a \"Developer IDE Console,\" a high-contrast workspace with code terminals and state monitors. I'm strategizing the layout: a hero section on deterministic agent compiling and a tab system covering the development lifecycle: Build, Simulate, Run, and Inspect. The file changes will impact the new file, `app/platforms/runtime-governance/page.tsx`.\n\n\n**Simulating Test Cycles**\n\nMy focus has shifted to simulating adversarial inputs within a cognitive run to demonstrate agent retry and self-correction loops. I'm working on the architecture diagram, planning an SVG multi-layer representation of developer tools, compilers, runtimes, and local sandboxes. The Bento Grid will spotlight key features like the GFF CLI and deterministic routing. I'm also planning an interactive tabbed console for \"Build\", \"Test\", \"Integrate\", and \"Operate\".\n\n\n"}}
