{"ts":"2026-06-26T06:59:13.272Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining the scope**\n\nI've determined the file ends at line 252. I am now focused on crafting Chunk 3C, ensuring it includes the telemetry sidebar panel, the Technical Bento Grid outlining our dev tool suite, relevant \"Next-Chapter\" links, and the Premium content.\n\n\n**Crafting the CTA**\n\nI'm now integrating the CTA section, focusing on finalizing the ending tags for Chunk 3C. I'm aiming for about 4500 characters, incorporating the Developer Telemetry Summary box, workspace stats, runtime baselines, and associated details within the given TypeScript structure.\n\n\n**Analyzing Telemetry Data**\n\nI'm currently delving into the specifics of the telemetry data. I am working on how to best render the active telemetry agents, average compile time, and build counts in an attractive and informative way. I am trying to determine the best visual representation of this information. I am also working on how to incorporate these elements within the overall design framework.\n\n\n**Refining the Presentation**\n\nI'm now focusing on refining the \"Live Trace\" section. I'm considering how to best present the local SDK's seamless container creation and secure code compilation into regional VPCs with TLS 1.3 encryption. I'm working on how best to represent this textually within the design framework. I am also working on section 3, which is the technical bento grid mapping out the developer ecosystem, and how to represent that.\n\n\n**Mapping the architecture**\n\nI'm now mapping out the \"BentoGrid\" component, focusing on the \"Static CLI Tooling\", \"Hermetic Sandboxing\", and \"Declarative Architecture\" components. I'm exploring how these elements contribute to the broader pipeline, considering their descriptions and associated icons. I am focusing on the user benefits that these provide and how to clearly articulate these benefits in the design.